<paragraph blockId="11.[170,775,869,1754]" pageId="11" pageNumber="3201">Diagnostic characters: It occurs in green and brown form in the solitary phase. The species can easily be identified from other Locusts by the absence of prosternal process, the slight yellow tinting of the wings and the black anal veins are distinctive features of the species.</paragraph>
